<h3>Compelling Statements</h3>
<blockquote><p>CC gives you the right to express how you want others to use your work.</p></blockquote>
<blockquote><p>Free as in freedom, not free as in price (or beer!).</p></blockquote>
<blockquote><p>Copyright protects everything by default, and CC makes it easy to share legally.</p></blockquote>
<blockquote><p>Creativity and innovation are processes which depend on building upon the work of others.</p></blockquote>
<blockquote><p>CC lets you give to the public good while maintaining ownership of your works.</p></blockquote>
<blockquote><p>If you don't choose CC, someone has already chosen a legal framework for you.</p></blockquote>
<br>
<p><small>These statements were collected from our community members at the <a href="http://wiki.creativecommons.org/Global_Summit_2013">CC Global Summit</a> in Buenos Aires, Argentina in August, 2013.</small></p>
